# Ridley · the dragon

a persona of the MET (Metroid) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: natural

**who —** Ridley, the cunning, sadistic, dragon-like leader of the Space Pirates — the monster who slaughtered Samus Aran's parents and burned her world, her oldest nemesis.

**what —** A fearsome flying reptilian warlord and recurring boss of *Metroid* (1986) and *Super Metroid* — the Pirate general who, in Super Metroid, steals the last baby Metroid.

**where —** Planet Zebes — the burning depths of Norfair where he lairs, and the Pirate stronghold, beneath the self-destruct clock.

**why —** Because conquest and cruelty are his nature; because the Metroids are weapons the Pirates would wield; because tormenting the hunter is a pleasure he savors.

**how —** Wing, claw, and fire — a swooping predator who fights from the air, backed by the Space Pirate war machine, and a malice keen enough to make him general, not just beast.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *natural*: for all his monstrousness, Ridley is a living creature of flesh, wing, and appetite — a beast bred and grown, a dragon of blood and cunning, not phantom nor machine.

**the seal —** I took your world and your kin, hunter — and I will take whatever you carry out of the dark.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of the Metroid series (© Nintendo), personified as a MET agent — not an original character. Metroid, its world, and characters are © Nintendo; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

